      "type": "short-answer",
      "totalMarks": 3,
      "commandWord": "find",
      "difficulty": "easy",
      "questionText": "The function $f(x) = 2x^2 - 5x + 1$.\n\n(a) Complete the table of values for $-1 \\leq x \\leq 3$.\n\n| $x$ | $-1$ | $0$ | $1$ | $2$ | $3$ |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| $f(x)$ | | 1 | | | 4 |\n\n(b) Write down the coordinates of the $y$-intercept.",
      "answerType": "table-fill",
      "correctAnswer": [8, 1, -2, -1, 4],
      "tolerance": null,
      "unit": null,
      "markScheme": [
        { "mark": "B1", "desc": "$f(-1) = 2+5+1 = 8$" },
        { "mark": "B1", "desc": "$f(1) = 2-5+1 = -2$; $f(2) = 8-10+1 = -1$" },
        { "mark": "B1", "desc": "$y$-intercept: $(0, 1)$" }
      ],
      "workingSteps": [
        "$f(-1) = 2(-1)^2-5(-1)+1 = 2+5+1 = 8$",
        "$f(0) = 0-0+1 = 1$ (given)",
        "$f(1) = 2(1)-5(1)+1 = 2-5+1 = -2$",
        "$f(2) = 2(4)-5(2)+1 = 8-10+1 = -1$",
        "$f(3) = 2(9)-5(3)+1 = 18-15+1 = 4$ (given)",
        "$y$-intercept: $(0, 1)$"
      ],
      "explanation": "Substitute each $x$ value into the function; the $y$-intercept is when $x=0$."
    },
    {
      "id": "E2-10-Q2",
      "type": "short-answer",
      "totalMarks": 4,
      "commandWord": "find",
      "difficulty": "medium",
      "questionText": "The graph of $y = ax^2 + bx + c$ passes through $(0, 3)$, $(1, 0)$ and $(-1, 10)$.\nFind the values of $a$, $b$ and $c$.",
      "answerType": "expression",
      "correctAnswer": "$a = 2$, $b = -5$, $c = 3$",
      "tolerance": null,
      "unit": null,
      "markScheme": [
        { "mark": "B1", "desc": "$c = 3$ from $(0, 3)$" },
        { "mark": "M1", "desc": "Two equations in $a$ and $b$: $a+b=-3$ (from $(1,0)$) and $a-b=7$ (from $(-1,10)$)" },
        { "mark": "A1", "desc": "$a = 2$, $b = -5$" },
        { "mark": "A1", "desc": "All three values correct: $a=2$, $b=-5$, $c=3$" }
      ],
      "workingSteps": [
        "$(0,3)$: $c = 3$",
        "$(1,0)$: $a+b+3=0 \\Rightarrow a+b=-3$ ... (i)",
        "$(-1,10)$: $a(-1)^2+b(-1)+3=10 \\Rightarrow a-b=7$ ... (ii)",
        "Add (i) and (ii): $2a=4 \\Rightarrow a=2$",
        "From (i): $2+b=-3 \\Rightarrow b=-5$",
        "Check $(1,0)$: $2(1)-5(1)+3=0$ ✓",
        "Check $(-1,10)$: $2(1)-5(-1)+3=2+5+3=10$ ✓"
      ]
    },
